  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Construction of urban collective memory maps based on social media data: a case study of Nanjing, China",
    "Bing Qiu foot_0, foot_1, Penghao Song 1,2, Xinran Tao 1,2, Qingyuan Zhou 1 & Fan Zhang 1 Rapid urbanization, which often overlooks the socio-cultural attributes and values embedded in urban space, has intensified problems of \"placelessness\" and a weakened sense of public identity.",
    "Examining city-public interactions through the concept of urban collective memory helps forge an operational, quantifiable link among the built environment, social identity, and historical continuity.",
    "Using Nanjing as a case study, this research integrates collective-memory theory with the urbanimage framework.",
    "Drawing on geotagged \"digital network memory\" data from social media, we apply natural-language processing (NLP) and geographic information system (GIS) techniques to aggregate individuals' spatial images and construct an urban collective-memory map comprising paths, nodes, landmarks, districts, and edges."
  ],
